Yet to be ascertained number of passengers have been burnt to ashes as two commercial vehicles travelling in opposite directions collided at Durum, 57km along the ever-busy Bauchi–Kano road. Reports from the State Command of FRSC revealed that occupants of the two commercial vehicles that were involved in a road crash were burnt to ashes. It was gathered that the accident involved a Ford Sharon and a Volkswagen vehicle, all commercial conveying goods. Eyewitnesses said that at least six passengers were seen burning in the vehicles that rammed into each other at about 12:15 pm. Sector Commander of the FRSC, Yusuf Abdullahi, said that more details about the accident will be available after the rescue operation and a report from the Ganjuwa LGA Station was received. Details later… 